---
layout: templates/documentation.njk
title: 'Documentation'
subtitle: 'Documenting the design and development process'
metaDescription: 'no metaDescription defined'
metaKeywords: 'user experience, eleventy, tailwind'
canonicalUrl: 'https://dataink.io'
bodyClasses: ''
contentClasses: 'bg-neutral-900'
---
<section class="space-y-8">
	<p>
		The portfolio now pulls content from the Sanity dataset. This page is a quick
		snapshot of the structures and relationships we fetch so you can see what is
		available to render and how the pieces fit together.
	</p>
	{{ collections.sanityOrganizations | dump | safe }}

{% set orgs = collections.sanityOrganizations or [] %}
	{% if orgs | length %}
		<div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-50 border border-neutral-700">
			<div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Organizations (Sanity)</h2>
					<p class="text-sm text-neutral-200">{{ orgs | length }} total organizations fetched directly from Sanity.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
				{% for org in orgs %}
					<li class="rounded-md border border-neutral-700 bg-neutral-900 p-3">
						<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-50">{{ org.title | default('Untitled organization') }}</p>
						{% if org.industry and org.industry.title %}
							<p class="text-xs text-neutral-300">Industry: {{ org.industry.title }}</p>
						{% endif %}
					</li>
				{% endfor %}
			</ul>
		</div>
	{% else %}
		<div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-50 border border-neutral-700">
			<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Organizations (Sanity)</h2>
			<p class="text-sm text-neutral-200">No organizations data is available yet. Ensure the Sanity fetch and collections are wired before build.</p>
		</div>
	{% endif %}
	<div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
		<div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-50 border border-neutral-700">
			<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Primary documents</h2>
			<ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-neutral-200">
				<li><strong>project</strong> — full portfolio case studies with hero, sections, SEO, and gallery</li>
				<li><strong>page</strong> — standalone pages (about, contact, etc.) with the same page object shape</li>
				<li><strong>organization</strong> — clients/companies linked from projects and awards</li>
				<li><strong>award</strong> — recognitions that can reference projects and organizations</li>
				<li><strong>post</strong> — articles and insights</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-50 border border-neutral-700">
			<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Taxonomies</h2>
			<ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-neutral-200">
				<li><strong>role</strong> — e.g., Design Director, UX Lead</li>
				<li><strong>activity</strong> — e.g., User Research, Visual Design (also drives PrinterMarks colors)</li>
				<li><strong>deliverable</strong> — outputs such as design systems or wireframes</li>
				<li><strong>industry</strong> — sector tags for filtering</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-50 border border-neutral-700">
		<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Embedded page shape</h2>
		<p class="text-sm text-neutral-200 mb-3">
			All page-like documents share the same structure, which we pull in one query so
			sections render consistently across the site:
		</p>
<pre class="text-xs bg-neutral-900 text-neutral-50 p-3 rounded overflow-x-auto">document → page {
	hero: heroBlock,
	sections: [section],
	seo: seoMeta
}</pre>
		<p class="text-sm text-neutral-200">
			Sections contain flexible blocks (mediaText, card, quoteBlock, imageGallery), each
			with nested media metadata so images and CTAs are ready for rendering without extra
			lookups.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-50 border border-neutral-700">
		<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Relationship highlights</h2>
		<ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-neutral-200">
			<li><strong>project.meta</strong> references <em>organization</em>, arrays of <em>roles</em>, <em>activities</em>, <em>deliverables</em>, and related <em>awards</em>.</li>
			<li><strong>award</strong> can reference both a <em>project</em> and an <em>organization</em> for cross-linking.</li>
			<li><strong>activity.color</strong> feeds the PrinterMarks overlay; keep slugs aligned with the JS mapping.</li>
			<li>Projects and posts are exposed as 11ty collections (<code>collections.projects</code>, <code>collections.posts</code>) after the Sanity fetch.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>

	<div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-50 border border-neutral-700">
		<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">What we pull in GROQ</h2>
		<p class="text-sm text-neutral-200 mb-3">
			Typical project query shape used in the build:
		</p>
<pre class="text-xs bg-neutral-900 text-neutral-50 p-3 rounded overflow-x-auto">*[_type == "project"] {
	page,
	meta {
		...,
		organization->,
		roles[]->,
		activities[]->,
		deliverables[]->,
		awards[]->
	},
	featuredImage,
	gallery
}</pre>
		<p class="text-sm text-neutral-200">
			This keeps referenced documents hydrated for rendering without additional requests.
			Filtering by taxonomy (e.g., activities) uses <code>references()</code> with the taxonomy slug.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-50 border border-neutral-700">
		<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Maintenance cues</h2>
		<ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-neutral-200">
			<li>Add new document types under <code>schemaTypes/documents/</code> and export via <code>schemaTypes/index.ts</code>.</li>
			<li>Update GROQ queries in the build when relationships change to keep 11ty collections in sync.</li>
			<li>PrinterMarks colors require matching <code>activity.slug</code> values in the frontend mapping.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</section>
